<page-title>The OpenMath Standard 2.0 Revision 1</page-title>

<p>
  We released Revision 1 of the OpenMath 2.0 Standard to acknowledge Content MathML as an OpenMath encoding, clarify the hexadecimal representation of OpenMath Floats and correct several smaller typos. This revision of the OpenMath 2.0 standard is intended as a fully backwards compatible erratum to the previous revision.  As such, no changes were made in the schema files and all valid OpenMath 2.0 Revision 0 objects remain valid OpenMath 2.0 Revision 1 objects and vice-versa. 
</p>

<p>The document is available in both XHTML and PDF formats.
To view the XHTML versions you need a browser with reasonable CSS support and
support for presentation MathML: both
Mozilla and Internet Explorer 6 display it correctly.</p>

<p>A ZIP archive of the files in this distribution including the DocBook sources and all necessary stylesheets <a href="om20.zip">is also available</a>. A ZIP archive of revision 0 can be <a href="om20r0.zip">found here</a>. </p>

